<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,582,861]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,267,727,753]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Remarks.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[275,522,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Podissus 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Stal" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[383,522,727,752]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Podisus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassimargo">crassimargo</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
has the anterolateral margin of the pronotum not emarginated and rugulose, and a well developed, spinose humeri; the peritreme does not reach the middle of the metapleuron, and the abdominal tubercle is short, barely reaching the metacoxa, and the femora are immaculate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
